&lt;li&gt;Work with product managers to establish, implement, and analyze product conversion funnels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering teams to ensure accurate and complete data collection for all new product launches and feature updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for product usage data requests from the design and product teams, providing them with the necessary insights to inform their decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bridge the communication and technical gap between the Product and Data departments, translating business needs into data requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor data quality and integrity, troubleshooting and resolving any issues related to event tracking or data loss.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in setting up and analyzing A/B tests and other experimental feature rollouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present regular reports and dashboards on product performance to stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years of experience as a Product Analyst or Product Owner with a strong analytical focus in a SaaS environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven hands-on&amp;nbsp; experience with advanced product analytics tools like Rudderstack, Segment or Userpilot including successful implementation and ongoing use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in web analytics platforms such as Google Analytics 4 (GA4) and Google Tag Manager (GTM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track-record with A/B testing and feature rollout initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a keen eye for detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively across different teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in data visualization tools (e.g., Looker Studio, Tableau, Power BI).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SQL for data querying and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
